The paper deals with the problem of selecting the most informative subset of variables in a graphical model, which is a fundamental issue in real-world systems such as sensor networks. This problem is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. The paper also leverages the theory of submodular functions, which is a topic in computer science related to optimization and algorithms, suggesting that cs.DS is another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information theory, which is a topic in computer science related to communication and data compression, suggesting that cs.IT is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper provides evidence of the effectiveness of the proposed method on real-world datasets, which suggests that cs.SI (social and information networks) is another possible sub-category.
